    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Prints intended for viewing through special peepshow devices, giving the illusion of three-dimensionality and movement. The subjects of perspective view prints are usually views of cities, events, Biblical stories, among others. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000061840/Kaldenbach, Perspective Views (1985)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000061841/Balzer, Peepshows: A Visual History (1998)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Druck, der dazu gedacht ist, durch spezielle Guckkastengeräte betrachtet zu werden und eine Illusion von Dreidimensionalität und Bewegung erzeugt. Die Motive der Guckkastenbilder sind unter anderem Stadtansichten, historische Ereignisse und biblische Geschichten.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Prenten die bedoeld zijn om in speciale kijkdoosachtige apparaten te worden bekeken, en die de illusie van driedimensionaliteit en beweging geven. In perspectiefprenten worden bijvoorbeeld steden, gebeurtenissen of Bijbelverhalen afgebeeld.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
